//Intradural extramedullary mass - I describe - Characterization I

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 of Spine MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Intradural extramedullary mass' from Finding dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' radio button
And I select 'Characterization I' tab

Then 'Localization' localizer is enabled
And 'Max. axial diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Max. craniocaudal diameter' input field is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening of the nerve' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled
And '"Target sign" (T2w central hypointense & peripheral hyperintense)' checkbox is enabled

And 'Hourglass shaped' checkbox is enabled
And 'Spindle-shaped' checkbox is enabled
